Bring a #saucepan{} of water up to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Trim the @courgette{1} then slice into rounds about 1cm thick. Trim the @spring onion{1} then slice thinly.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on a high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the courgette and cook on each side until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

Remove from the pan to a clean #chopping board{} or #plate{} and allow to cool.

Once the water for the pasta is boiling, add the @linguine{200%g} and simmer until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the pan, drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile return the frying pan to medium high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

When hot, add the @chorizo{90%g}(sliced), fry until the chorizo is golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the garlic and @chilli flakes{pinch} (use less if you don't like heat - you can always add more later if you want!) and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @tomato passata{1}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, @water{750%ml} and @vegetable stock powder{1}.

Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> If you've decided to add chorizo to your meal, add to the pan before you add the garlic, chilli
flakes etc. Fry until the chorizo is golden, 2-3 mins, add the garlic and chilli flakes (add less if
you don't like heat) and continue with the step and recipe as instructed.

Add the @king prawns{150%g} to the tomato sauce, stir together and simmer until cooked, ~{4-5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, roughly chop up the courgette and add to a #small bowl{} with the spring onion and another @chilli flakes{pinch} (use less chilli if you don't like heat).

Add the drained pasta to the pan of tomato sauce along with the cheese. Mix well to combine, then season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> Add a splash more water if the liquid has evaporated too much.

Share between your #bowls{}. Spoon over the charred courgette mixture.

Enjoy!